  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We currently have `beacon_previous_live_validators` and `beacon_previous_active_validators` which together can be used to calculate participation rate. However, this estimate seems to be on the high side.\r\n\r\nI believe this is because `beacon_previous_live_validators` only accounts for getting the correct source checkpoint, whereas for finalisation purposes we care about getting both the correct source and the correct target.\r\n\r\nSo, my proposal is, create a `beacon_previous_correct_validators` metric (and a version for the current epoch) that tracks the count of validators making attestations with both the correct source and target (ignoring head/block_root).\r\n\r\nThis will allow us a more accurate view of proximity to finalisation, and likely matches what other clients are doing.",
